@page "/Statistics"

<MudTimeline>
    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Primary" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 1</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:fitness_center" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Primary" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Initial Gains</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">During the first year, most beginners experience rapid strength gains and muscle growth due to increased neuromuscular adaptation. Visible muscle growth starts to appear.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Info" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Info" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 2</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:trending_up" Color="Color.Info" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Info" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Consistency and Progression</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">By the second year, you’ll see more noticeable muscle definition and growth. Progress slows slightly but continues with proper training and nutrition.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Success" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Success" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 3</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:check_circle" Color="Color.Success" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Success" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Solid Muscle Foundation</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">At this stage, the muscle base is well-developed. Continued gains may be slower, but strength and muscle endurance have improved significantly.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Warning" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Warning" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 4-5</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:fitness_center" Color="Color.Warning" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Warning" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Building More Mass</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">By now, your muscle gains are more focused on quality and size. Advanced training techniques like periodization and progressive overload become essential for continued growth.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Error" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Error" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 6-7</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:arrow_upward" Color="Color.Error" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Error" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Plateau Phase</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">During these years, muscle growth may slow down as you hit plateaus. Focus on varying your routine and optimizing recovery and nutrition for new growth.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Dark" Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
            <MudText Color="Color.Dark" Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Year 8+</MudText>
        </ItemOpposite>
        <ItemContent>
            <MudIcon Icon="icons:star" Color="Color.Dark" Size="Size.Medium" />
            <MudText Color="Color.Dark" Typo="Typo.body1" GutterBottom="true">Maximized Muscle Growth</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">By the 8th year and beyond, muscle mass has reached its peak. However, continued focus on strength, recovery, and fine-tuning your nutrition can help maintain and optimize muscle size.</MudText>
        </ItemContent>
    </MudTimelineItem>

    <MudTimelineItem Size="Size.Small">
        <ItemOpposite>
        </ItemOpposite>
    </MudTimelineItem>
</MudTimeline>


